  "local_port": 49078,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Clean Master, the Android app, deleted some of my important pictures when I tapped the \"clean the junk\" option. What are some methods to retrieve the pictures?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that Clean Master deleted your important photos. Fortunately, there are several methods you can try to recover your lost pictures. Here's a step-by-step guide to help you retrieve them:\n\n### 1. **Check the \"Recently Deleted\" or \"Trash\" Folder**\n\nMany Android devices and gallery apps have a built-in recycle bin where deleted photos are temporarily stored before being permanently removed.\n\n- **For Google Photos:**\n  - Open the **Google Photos** app.\n  - Tap on **Library** at the bottom.\n  - Select **Trash**.\n  - If your photos are there, select the ones you want to recover and tap **Restore**.\n\n- **For Samsung Gallery:**\n  - Open the **Gallery** app.\n  - Tap on **Albums**.\n  - Look for a **Trash** or **Recycle Bin** folder.\n  - Restore the desired photos.\n\n### 2. **Restore from Cloud Backups**\n\nIf you had set up cloud backups, you might be able to retrieve your photos from there.\n\n- **Google Photos Backup:**\n  - Visit [Google Photos](https://photos.google.com/) on your device or computer.\n  - Sign in with the same Google account used on your Android device.\n  - Check the **Photos** and **Trash** sections for your missing pictures.\n\n- **Other Cloud Services:**\n  - If you use services like **Dropbox**, **OneDrive**, or **Amazon Photos**, check their respective apps or websites for backups.\n\n### 3. **Use Data Recovery Apps**\n\nThere are several Android apps designed to recover deleted photos. **Note**: Most effective methods may require **root access**, and rooting your device can void warranties or cause other issues. Proceed with caution.\n\n- **DiskDigger:**\n  - Install **DiskDigger** from the [Google Play Store](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.defiantcoder.diskdigger).\n  - Open the app and grant the necessary permissions.\n  - Choose **Basic Scan** (no root required) or **Full Scan** (requires root) for deeper recovery.\n  - Browse through the recoverable photos and save them to your device or SD card.\n\n- **Dr.Fone - Data Recovery (Android):**\n  - Download and install **Dr.Fone** on your PC from [Wondershare's website](https://drfone.wondershare.com/android-data-recovery.html).\n  - Connect your Android device to the PC via USB.\n  - Follow the on-screen instructions to scan and recover deleted photos.\n\n### 4. **Use a PC-Based Data Recovery Tool**\n\nIf the above apps don't work, you can try PC-based recovery tools. This method often provides a higher chance of recovery but might require more technical steps.\n\n- **Steps:**\n  1. **Enable USB Debugging on Your Android Device:**\n     - Go to **Settings** > **About phone**.\n     - Tap **Build number** seven times to enable **Developer options**.\n     - Go back to **Settings**, then **Developer options**.\n     - Enable **USB debugging**.\n\n  2. **Connect to PC:**\n     - Use a USB cable to connect your Android device to your computer.\n\n  3. **Run Recovery Software:**\n     - Install and launch a recovery tool like **Recuva** or **Dr.Fone** on your PC.\n     - Follow the software instructions to scan your device for deleted photos.\n     - Recover and save the photos to your PC.\n\n### 5. **Professional Data Recovery Services**\n\nIf the photos are extremely important and the above methods don't work, consider reaching out to a professional data recovery service. They have advanced tools and expertise to retrieve data from damaged or tampered devices. **Note**: This can be costly and isn't always guaranteed to succeed.\n\n### **Tips to Increase Recovery Success:**\n\n- **Minimize Device Usage:** After deletion, avoid taking new photos or installing apps to prevent overwriting the deleted data.\n- **Act Quickly:** The sooner you attempt recovery, the higher the chances of success.\n- **Regular Backups:** To prevent future data loss, regularly back up your important photos to cloud services or external storage.\n\n### **Preventive Measures for the Future:**\n\n- **Disable Aggressive Cleaning Apps:** Some cleaning apps can mistakenly delete important files. Use them cautiously or disable automatic cleaning features.\n- **Regular Backups:** Use Google Photos or other backup services to automatically save copies of your photos.\n- **Review Cleaning Settings:** Ensure that essential folders or apps are excluded from cleaning operations.\n\nI hope one of these methods helps you recover your important photos. If you encounter any issues or need further assistance, feel free to ask!",
